HEADWORD: Effectuate
<hw>Ef*fec"tu*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Effectuated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Effectuating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>effectuer</ets>. See <er>Effect</er>, <pos>n.</pos> & <pos>v.
t.</pos>]</ety> <def>To bring to pass; to effect; to achieve; to
accomplish; to fulfill.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A fit instrument to <qex>effectuate</qex> his desire.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir P. Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In order to <qex>effectuate</qex> the thorough reform.</q>
<rj><qau>G. T. Curtis.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Effectuation</ent>⟦br⟧
